        <Sticky classid="Sticky" id="1621984682" x="36" y="18" w="918" h="90" colors="0, 15792890">
          <paramlist>
            <param name="full_font" value="Times New Roman, 9pt" />
            <param name="align" value="0" />
            <param name="fg_color_adv" value="#FF000000" />
            <param name="bg_color_adv" value="#FFFFFFFF" />
            <param name="hl_color_adv" value="#FFFFFF00" />
            <param name="bdr_color_adv" value="#FFFFFFFF" />
            <param name="arrows" value="0" />
            <param name="style" value="1" />
            <param name="font" value="1" />
            <param name="fg_color" value="0" />
            <param name="bg_color" value="15792890" />
          </paramlist><![CDATA[This example shows how to compute the closed-loop (CL) and open-loop (OL) transfer functions (TF) of a system composed of a PI controller acting on a second order low-pass filter with time delay. 
To compute the CL TF, the scan block is placed at the input of the system and the output is measured, while for the OL case the scan block breaks the loop between the controller and the plant so as to measure the OL transfer function.
The CL TF is typically used for dynamic performance evaluation while the OL TF is useful for controller design.]]></Sticky>
        <User classid="UserCmp" id="1067005407" name="master:annotation" x="396" y="126" w="58" h="38" z="1" orient="0" defn="master:annotation" link="-1" q="4" disable="false">
